        conseils: "The belfry can be visited (€5, 200 steps) and the view over the town and Douaisis plain is magnificent. Carillon concerts take place on Saturday mornings (11am) in summer — settle into a café on the Grand'Place to enjoy them. The Chartreuse Museum (€6, closed Tuesdays) deserves at least 1h30: the cloister is superb and the Flemish painting collection rivals Lille's. The Gayant Festival (first weekend of July) is an extraordinary spectacle: the giants parade through the streets for three days, accompanied by brass bands, floats and thousands of spectators. Book your taxi well in advance for this period. The Scarpe quayside, with its barges and terraces, is the ideal spot for a waterside lunch. Douai's andouillettes are renowned throughout the region.",
